(8949, 'frFR', 'Hmmm... strangely enough I don\'t feel any better about my brother\'s death at the hands of those brutes.$B$BWell, you held your end of the bargain. &nbsp;Let\'s see what I can do for you.', 18019),
(8950, 'frFR', 'Yes, these will do just fine. &nbsp;After I\'m done, no force in the world will be able to stop your victim from accepting your challenge.', 18019),
(8951, 'frFR', 'I can\'t believe our lives are all but forfeit all because of a stupid medallion! &nbsp;And you\'re sure Anthion mentioned Bodley?$B$BWell, you\'ve done your job so let\'s get your reward out of the way.', 18019),
